  "title": "Investment Broker",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Portfolio Management:</strong> Build, monitor, and adjust tailored investment portfolios for high-net-worth clients.</li><li><strong>Advisory & Strategy:</strong> Offer expert investment advice on asset allocation and financial planning, ensuring alignment with client objectives and risk appetite.</li><li><strong>Business Development:</strong> Actively acquire new clients, retain relationships, and, in some models, handle transaction executions as a broker.</li><li><strong>Market Analysis:</strong> Stay updated on economic trends, market volatility, and investment products to provide timely advice.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Adhere strictly to internal policies, ethical standards, and regulatory requirements (e.g., MAS in Singapore).</li><li><strong>Client Reporting:</strong> Prepare and present performance reports to clients. </li></ul>",
